x4freetext: Thin circular foils of 99.46% 205-Tl /0.54% 203-Te/
were fabricated by pressing in an appropriate mold.
The thickness varied from 630 to 296 mu-g/cm**2. The
thinnest foils were used in the energy region of 40
to 50 MeV to obtain more detail on the excitation
function.

x4freetext: /By author/ Cross section is not corrected for
contribution of the 203TI(p,4n) 200Pb reaction
since it is not well-known in this region. Results
from `B0168.002` indicated that up to 40 MeV the
principal contribution to the thin-target yield is
from 203-Tl(p,4n) 200-Pb even though this isotope is
present only as 0.54%.
